1
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:51,958
[PILOT 3A]
Man, check it out.


2
00:00:52,041 --> 00:00:53,458
Never seen that mecha before.


3
00:00:53,541 --> 00:00:54,625
Is it new?

4
00:00:54,708 --> 00:00:56,166
[PILOT 3B]
That's Lieutenant Leroy's mecha,

5
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:58,416
the Primavera Delta.

6
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:01,416
Right. The new hottie pilot
who just got posted here.

7
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:05,083
Which explains why it looks
like a giant blowup doll.

8
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:07,333
You guys might wanna
keep your voices down.

9
00:01:07,416 --> 00:01:08,375
[BOTH gasp]

10
00:01:14,166 --> 00:01:15,083
[PILOTS]
Ten-hut!

11
00:01:15,166 --> 00:01:16,666
[PILOT 3A]
Good day, Lieutenant!

12
00:01:18,583 --> 00:01:20,333
[LIGIER]
Subaru Ichinose, is that right?

13
00:01:20,416 --> 00:01:22,375
[SUBARU gasping]

14
00:01:22,458 --> 00:01:23,416
[SUBARU]
That smell.

15
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:25,000
What could it be?

16
00:01:25,083 --> 00:01:26,541
[gasps]

17
00:01:26,625 --> 00:01:28,000
[LIGIER] Have you received the
update about your Durandal?

18
00:01:28,083 --> 00:01:30,416
If not, I need you to
get ahold of my Papa.

19
00:01:30,500 --> 00:01:34,083
[SUBARU]
Get a hold of her... "tatas"?

20
00:01:34,166 --> 00:01:35,500
[VENTURI]
Thank you, Lieutenant!

21
00:01:35,583 --> 00:01:38,541
I told you I would get in touch
with him on my own time.

22
00:01:38,625 --> 00:01:40,416
And while we're on the <i>Tiramisu,</i>

23
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:42,666
I am not your Papa,
I'm your Captain!

24
00:01:42,750 --> 00:01:44,666
Yes, Captain! Roger that!

25
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:47,125
[gasps] She's his daughter?

26
00:01:47,208 --> 00:01:48,625
[VENTURI]
Subaru Ichinose.

27
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:49,791
[SUBARU]
Sir!

28
00:01:49,875 --> 00:01:51,208
[VENTURI]
This is not up for discussion.

29
00:01:51,291 --> 00:01:52,500
Effective immediately,

30
00:01:52,583 --> 00:01:55,416
Ligier Leroy will
pilot the Durandal.

31
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:58,625
You will graciously take her
place aboard the Primavera.

32
00:01:58,708 --> 00:02:00,125
[gasping]

33
00:02:02,583 --> 00:02:05,750
Subaru, can you hear me?
It's not that bad, all right.

34
00:02:05,833 --> 00:02:07,208
She's his daughter.

35
00:02:07,291 --> 00:02:09,416
What's he supposed
to do, tell her "no"?

36
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:10,625
Come on.

37
00:02:10,708 --> 00:02:13,000
You can't just shut
down on me like this.

38
00:02:13,083 --> 00:02:15,166
Listen. I know it's weird.

39
00:02:15,250 --> 00:02:17,125
You've got a lot of miles
with the Durandal

40
00:02:17,208 --> 00:02:18,791
and it's a little like
sawing off your arm...

41
00:02:18,875 --> 00:02:20,125
[beeping]

42
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:21,375
[CODY]
Subaru! Incoming!

43
00:02:21,458 --> 00:02:22,583
[SUBARU]
Hostiles?

44
00:02:25,666 --> 00:02:26,791
[SUBARU]
I look like an easy target

45
00:02:26,875 --> 00:02:28,791
because I'm inside
a woman... robot.

46
00:02:28,875 --> 00:02:30,041
Woman Robot.

47
00:02:30,125 --> 00:02:31,583
They don't know it's me.

48
00:02:31,666 --> 00:02:33,166
Or they do and they're attacking
because I'm an embarrassment

49
00:02:33,250 --> 00:02:36,041
to my gender. Or worse.

50
00:02:36,125 --> 00:02:38,250
Uh. They'll think I'm a freak.

51
00:02:38,333 --> 00:02:40,625
A crossdressing,
pink-loving freak!

52
00:02:40,708 --> 00:02:42,375
They'll all laugh at me
when they get home!

53
00:02:42,458 --> 00:02:45,291
And why wouldn't they?!
I'm frilly!

54
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:48,541
[SUBARU]
No!

55
00:02:48,625 --> 00:02:51,208
I hate it! Make it stop!

56
00:02:51,291 --> 00:02:52,708
I may as well be
working the streets

57
00:02:52,791 --> 00:02:55,416
or on my way to grandmother's
house to deliver cookies.

58
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:57,333
I can't take this anymore!

59
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:01,125
I'm a man! I'm a man!

60
00:03:01,208 --> 00:03:03,666
I'm a man!

61
00:03:05,291 --> 00:03:08,333
[SUBARU] How am I even supposed
to fight in this thing?

62
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:10,916
[gasps]

63
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:13,750
[SUBARU]
It smells like... shampoo.

64
00:03:13,833 --> 00:03:16,375
Lieutenant Leroy's lady musk.

65
00:03:17,375 --> 00:03:18,625
[SUBARU]
That's right.

66
00:03:18,708 --> 00:03:20,041
I forgot, I'm inside her pink--

67
00:03:20,125 --> 00:03:22,500
Subaru, I need you
to focus here!

68
00:03:22,583 --> 00:03:25,458
[SUBARU]
I'm in... a girl's room.

69
00:03:25,541 --> 00:03:27,875
[NARRATOR]
Poor young Subaru Ichinose.

70
00:03:27,958 --> 00:03:29,333
Barely 19.

71
00:03:29,416 --> 00:03:31,208
He's spent what should
be the best days

72
00:03:31,291 --> 00:03:34,625
of his formative youth
trapped in outer space.

73
00:03:35,166 --> 00:03:36,666
I'm doin' it!

74
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:43,208
[SUBARU] Time to grab me
some steel tatas!

75
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:46,458
[NARRATOR] Which is where
his brain remains today.

76
00:03:47,708 --> 00:03:50,250
Shouldn't be too hard
to find him.

77
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:53,833
Don't do that!

78
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:55,375
You idiot!

79
00:03:55,458 --> 00:03:56,416
You can't touch those!

80
00:03:56,500 --> 00:03:58,791
[yelling]

81
00:04:02,125 --> 00:04:04,291
Or they will explode.

82
00:04:04,375 --> 00:04:07,916
Too late. Good news is,
he makes dumb look cute.

83
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,750
[NARRATOR] Miraculously,
Subaru returned to base

84
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,875
with only minor burns

85
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:18,125
[footsteps]

86
00:04:18,208 --> 00:04:19,375
[VULGAR grunts]
Hey.

87
00:04:19,458 --> 00:04:21,166
Whatcha doin' in there,
Powder Puff?

88
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:24,041
That mech isn't gonna
fly itself, now is it?

89
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:26,833
Uh, no, mostly because
I don't have one anymore.

90
00:04:26,916 --> 00:04:29,041
Thanks for bringing it up.

91
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:30,458
Ha, ha. That's right.

92
00:04:30,541 --> 00:04:33,041
You've been in here ball
scratchin' so you don't know.

93
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:35,916
The Durandal Full Model
Change just came in.

94
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:39,000
[SUBARU gasps]
Wait, what?

95
00:04:39,083 --> 00:04:41,166
Did you say I have a new mecha?

96
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:44,041
A cockpit that
only I will handle?

97
00:04:45,583 --> 00:04:48,291
You'd be a fool to ride it
without a good manual first,

98
00:04:48,375 --> 00:04:49,500
wouldn't ya?

99
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:52,500
[gasping] Ha, ha! Later!

100
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,708
--[SHIGERUKO laughs]
--[VULGAR] What a douche.

101
00:04:54,791 --> 00:04:56,875
[NARRATOR] Subaru's heart
throbbed with excitement

102
00:04:56,958 --> 00:05:00,625
as he nestled into the warmth
of his very own cockpit.

103
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:03,166
[sighs]

104
00:05:04,666 --> 00:05:06,583
Oh, c'mon they gave
me volume two!

105
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:08,666
[INTERCOM VOICE 1A]
Durandal launching!

106
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:11,666
[SUBARU]
This is nuts.

107
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:14,416
I figured the basics would be
pretty much the same for both.

108
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:17,541
But the new Durandal's cockpit
is way more complicated!

109
00:05:17,625 --> 00:05:19,083
Forget battling the enemy.

110
00:05:19,166 --> 00:05:21,750
I can't even make it
back to the <i>Tiramisu.</i>

111
00:05:21,833 --> 00:05:23,916
What kind of jerk-off
doesn't know how to handle

112
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,791
his own damn equipment?

113
00:05:26,416 --> 00:05:28,000
[INTERCOM VOICE 1A]
Switching to F Flyer Mode.

114
00:05:28,083 --> 00:05:29,083
[SUBARU]
Uh?

115
00:05:31,166 --> 00:05:33,333
How the hell did it transform?

116
00:05:34,458 --> 00:05:35,666
[SUBARU]
That's really nifty and all,

117
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:38,125
but I still don't know how
to pilot this thing!

118
00:05:38,208 --> 00:05:39,750
Uh? Asteroids?

119
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:41,583
Now is not the time to crash!

120
00:05:41,666 --> 00:05:45,166
C'mon Durandal Freakin' F!
Help me out here, man! Uh?!

121
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:46,375
This is this it.

122
00:05:46,458 --> 00:05:47,541
[ANNOUNCER 3A]
It looks like last year's...

123
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:48,583
[SUBARU] Why would
I need a split screen?

124
00:05:48,666 --> 00:05:49,791
I can't see!

125
00:05:49,875 --> 00:05:52,750
Of course the support
center is closed!

126
00:05:52,833 --> 00:05:55,541
That's it. It's all over.

127
00:05:55,625 --> 00:05:57,958
I can feel time slowing down.

128
00:05:58,041 --> 00:05:59,583
I must not have
survived the crash

129
00:05:59,666 --> 00:06:02,000
and am falling into
death's arms.

130
00:06:03,041 --> 00:06:04,416
[SUBARU]
Weep not.

131
00:06:04,500 --> 00:06:06,416
This is the way
I would've wanted it.

132
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:09,583
The cockpit will forever
be my sanctuary.

133
00:06:09,666 --> 00:06:10,416
[gasps]

134
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,000
Hey there, Pee Pants!

135
00:06:12,083 --> 00:06:14,166
Couldn't figure out
split screen, huh?

136
00:06:14,250 --> 00:06:15,458
Yeah, neither could I.

137
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:16,708
Lieutenant Hummer?

138
00:06:16,791 --> 00:06:18,833
It'll go away if you press
the glowing button

139
00:06:18,916 --> 00:06:19,708
for three seconds.

140
00:06:19,791 --> 00:06:21,333
I'll remember that.

141
00:06:30,166 --> 00:06:31,625
[SUBARU]
I'm still alive.

142
00:06:31,708 --> 00:06:34,833
Now back to the sunken
ship of broken dreams.

143
00:06:34,916 --> 00:06:38,333
Freakin' <i>Tiramisu</i> and
all its A-hole crew.

144
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:40,083
[gasps]

145
00:06:43,958 --> 00:06:46,125
[SUBARU] What?
They're all in Durandal Fs?

146
00:06:46,208 --> 00:06:47,041
Oh.

147
00:06:47,125 --> 00:06:49,208
So it's a mass production model.

148
00:06:49,291 --> 00:06:50,500
Of course.

149
00:06:50,583 --> 00:06:52,000
Why would they ever trust me

150
00:06:52,083 --> 00:06:54,416
with my own personal
mecha again?

151
00:06:57,083 --> 00:06:58,416
[NARRATOR]
And with that,

152
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:02,166
Subaru clung even more
tightly to his cockpit.

